body: I haven't been following jQuery UI development; do you know what sorts of changes have been made? Assuming everything works as expected, I'm fine requiring 5.0.

The work since the last version (4.2.1 -- April 21 2014) was done in the last week. It brings the gem up to snuff with jquery-ui 1.11.x, which has a different set of naming/file conventions. Otherwise only housekeeping things like READMEs and Gem development files.

I just noticed the same thing after upgrading from 0.6.3. Locking jquery-ui-rails to 4.x works. jquery-ui 1.11 is mostily about AMD support (the reason for the filename changes):
http://jqueryui.com/upgrade-guide/1.11/

jquery-ui-rails changed the way one must reference a module in their manifests
in v5.0.0 from a `.` to a `/`. Since base.js.coffee uses the dot syntax, we
should set the upper limit of the gem version for now.

See: https://github.com/joliss/jquery-ui-rails/commit/774f8b3e2e5ae8b80515128dd0cdb5cde48dfc01

Fixes #3247.

issue.title: Fix jquery ui asset

repository.name: activeadmin
repository.description: The administration framework for Ruby on Rails applications.

issue.body:
_Problem:_
I stumbled upon an issue where active admin throws error `couldn't find file 'jquery.ui.datepicker'`, I have looked at issue #2232, and checked the `jquery-ui-rails` gem version in `Gemfile.lock`, it already had the correct version, unfortunately in my case it still throws errors.

_Solution:_
I checked on jquery-ui-rails (https://github.com/joliss/jquery-ui-rails), and noticed that it uses a different way of adding asset, which uses `jquery-ui/datepicker` instead of the one used in `base.js.coffee` which uses `jquery.ui.datepicker`, hopefully this satisfies other users that had the same issue.

_Tested On:_
Mac OSX 10.9.3
Ruby 2.1.2
